00:28:59.370 --> 00:29:02.220
The amygdala, the hippocampus,
the hypothalamus --

00:29:02.220 --> 00:29:05.070
these are the parts of the brain
that quickly spot what's going on,

00:29:05.070 --> 00:29:06.710
try to figure out very
quickly what it is.

00:29:06.710 --> 00:29:10.020
It's like going to a file cabinet
and decide what's the action to it.

00:29:10.020 --> 00:29:13.350
And so if I take this and
so -- is Bob, is that it?

00:29:13.350 --> 00:29:15.810
Yeah, if I throw this at Bob,
he's not going to say, "Oh,

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:17.110
what happens when it gets here?"

00:29:17.110 --> 00:29:19.760
You know, his hand will
shoot up instinctively.

00:29:19.760 --> 00:29:21.220
It's a protection mechanism.

00:29:21.220 --> 00:29:22.520
And it can save our lives.

00:29:22.520 --> 00:29:24.950 position:56%
You're driving in the morning and
the car stops short in front of you.

00:29:24.950 --> 00:29:26.340
You see those taillights going.

00:29:26.340 --> 00:29:28.430
You don't say to yourself,
"What's the best thing to do now?"

00:29:28.430 --> 00:29:29.810
Or you'd be in their back seat.

00:29:29.810 --> 00:29:32.550
Your foot hits the brake before
you get a chance to think about it.

00:29:32.550 --> 00:29:36.240
This is where the heart of a lot
of our core stereotypes come from.

00:29:36.240 --> 00:29:38.680
Quick assessment to that person.

00:29:38.680 --> 00:29:42.240
Quick association -- put
myself into friend or foe mode.

00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:43.910
And we're particularly
sensitive to foe.

00:29:43.910 --> 00:29:46.810
We look first to eliminate
foe before we see friend.

00:29:46.810 --> 00:29:48.400
So we can see this
again in the brain.

00:29:48.400 --> 00:29:51.470
It takes about 20% more
brain energy, fluid,

00:29:51.470 --> 00:29:53.900
et cetera to see something
friendly than it has

00:29:53.900 --> 00:29:56.220
to see something negative
because the brain wants

00:29:56.220 --> 00:29:58.230
to make sure it's safe before
it will allow things in.

00:29:58.230 --> 00:30:02.470
And this is why, of course, the
